Subject: Re: ignition folly

>greetings, on my 69 bus the key was pulled, and the ignition stayed on. the
>car cut out as in stalled. both idiot lights remained glowing and the key
>will no longer re-enter the cylinder. i disconnected the battery for now.
>i'm looking for suggestions on how to get the key in, thanks in adv., steve

As you don't have a steering lock you could replace the key function with a
switch and push button to get you going while you work out the problem with
the ignition.

This page has instructions for replacing a 71 to 74 ignition switch which may
have some relevance to you as well:

http://www.specialpatrolgroup.co.uk/spooky/barrel/barrel.html

Martin
